ce='Tahoma' size='2'>Mob Level</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>12 - 14</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Location</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Underwater Cave</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Factions</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Not known</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Spells Used</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Heat Blood, Numb the dead, Grasping roots, Endure Cold, Ward Undead</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Strategy</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#000000' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'>Look around in the cave until you find a 2 spawn of Ice Boned Skeletons (shouldn't take long).  Go down the hall and bind yourself cause you are going to die.  That is the sad but very true reality.<br><br>

When you are done, summon your level 12 pet and make sure it is level 11.  Now cast Endure Cold on both of you.<br><br>

Now it gets dangerous.  Find the weakest one and cast Numb the Dead.  The other will charge you. Immediately cast Heat Blood and send in pet.  Now step in to take some hits so Heat Blood can start working.  Now step back and Ward Ward Ward until dead.  Now the skeleton that was Numbed should have come after you or stayed there.  Try to work in an extra Numb the dead while you are fighting.  When he comes at you, skip Heat Blood and just Ward Undead until it comes after you.  This is very dangerous but it is the only way.  You are probably going to die if anything goes wrong, but that is ok.  Just work on at least killing one so when you come back, you will only have one to deal with.<br><br>

Now the spawn is very fast and the XP is very good, but it is very dangerous.  I started hunting at 16 and it was easy, and the XP was 1 1/2 bubble per hour.  I can't imagine what it would be at 12 or 13.  Although the loot isn't good, the XP is great.  Hope you like it as much as I did =)</td></tr><tr><td width='98' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma' size='2'>Author</td><td width='499' align='left' bgcolor='#21456B' height='22' valign='middle'><font color='#FFFFFF' face='Tahoma'size='2'><a href ='mailto:'>Stanima</td></tr><tr></table><br><br><table border='0' width=611><tr><td width='100%' colspan='2' bgcolor='#21456B'><p align='left' style='word-spacing: 0; margin: 0'><b><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Additional Comments</font></b></td></tr><td width='17%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>Moxxer</font></td><td width='83%'><font color='#FFFFFF' size='2' face='Tahoma'>I must say that I died many many times trying to get to the cave. You better have your swimming to 60 or above, i also recomend that you get a Shaman to buff you with Agilty spells to make you swim faster (I lost 4 boubles of XP trying to get to this cave).<br><br>

Once you enter the cave BIND!!! I can’t say this more. I was with my friend Harak (Shaman), and we started looking around for this camp of Skeletons. Well, first we ran into a veary big Ice bar that kicked our little butts. After rebuffing and adding some SoWs we got our corpses and went searching the other derection.<br><br>

Next came a veary large pet Skeleton that belongs to Lich. He dosen’t like Necros so watch out. After dying a few times from him (he runs around the cave by the way) we found the Ice Bar again and died once again. After that we were buffing back up to leave this place of death, but just as we were leaving the Ice Bar comes a chasing from behind us, attacking me. So off we where into the water. Just making it to the hole in the ice as my last breath of air was gone.<br><br>

The ice bar dos not chase from cave, or he just can’t swim well because I did not look back :)<br><br>

Other comments:<br><br>

If you die in the water trying to get to cave, don’t fret. You can just summon your corpse from above the water as i did lots of times</font></td></tr></table></td></table></div>